WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.483 --> 00:00:01.750
Previously
on "Criminal Minds"...

2
00:00:02.396 --> 00:00:04.113
The press has named him
the prince of darkness.

3
00:00:04.704 --> 00:00:06.070
The dark
is his signature.

4
00:00:06.122 --> 00:00:07.739
And we'll find that he's
always killed this way.

5
00:00:07.776 --> 00:00:10.060
He's shows up during a blackout. he robs.
he kills. he leaves a witness.

6
00:00:10.112 --> 00:00:12.530
He got away with it for 26 years.
Why did he come back?

7
00:00:12.581 --> 00:00:14.231
Joe and Sylvia
Spicer were killed.

8
00:00:14.333 --> 00:00:15.499
Those are my parents.

9
00:00:15.567 --> 00:00:16.784
Why is he doing this?

10
00:00:16.902 --> 00:00:18.386
He keeps a survivor
so they'll never forget him.

11
00:00:18.453 --> 00:00:20.503
But with you.
it goes beyond that.

12
00:00:20.513 --> 00:00:22.713
He believes he turned you
into the city's hero.

13
00:00:22.723 --> 00:00:23.943
And he wants that recognition..

14
00:00:24.040 --> 00:00:25.257
He wants everyone
to know what he's done.

15
00:00:25.325 --> 00:00:26.708
Is that your daughter?
Where is she?

16
00:00:26.793 --> 00:00:27.709
She's with my sister.

17
00:00:27.794 --> 00:00:29.177
That's Morgan
on the other line.

18
00:00:29.262 --> 00:00:30.462
We're gonna need him
at Kristin's house.

19
00:00:30.513 --> 00:00:31.496
Let's get over there.

20
00:00:31.548 --> 00:00:32.998
This is about you.
There's no history

21
00:00:33.049 --> 00:00:35.067
at your sister's place.
He probably took them to Santa Monica

22
00:00:35.134 --> 00:00:36.218
to your old house.

23
00:00:38.271 --> 00:00:40.672
It's only a matter of time
before the cell phone reception goes.

24
00:00:40.723 --> 00:00:41.723
We lost Morgan.

25
00:00:41.808 --> 00:00:43.275
Reid? Great.

26
00:00:43.342 --> 00:00:46.344
Put the gun down
or she dies.

27
00:00:46.396 --> 00:00:47.679
No. pick it up!
Pick it up!

28
00:00:47.730 --> 00:00:48.897
On your knees.

29
00:00:48.982 --> 00:00:52.251
Don't do it!
Don't do this! Don't!

30
00:00:53.353 --> 00:00:54.570
No!

31
00:00:54.654 --> 00:00:56.488
What is wrong with you?!

32
00:00:58.074 --> 00:00:59.524
No!

33
00:00:59.576 --> 00:01:01.543
We will find you.
you sick son of a bitch.

34
00:01:01.628 --> 00:01:03.278
Is that another promise?

35
00:01:03.346 --> 00:01:05.714
Please. please...Aah!

36
00:01:05.798 --> 00:01:09.001
Ellie. I will find you!

37
00:01:15.875 --> 00:01:19.411
Leonard Cohen:
♪ I went down to the place ♪

38
00:01:19.479 --> 00:01:20.963
♪ where I knew
she lay waiting ♪

39
00:01:21.030 --> 00:01:25.484
♪ under the marble
and the snow ♪

40
00:01:25.551 --> 00:01:28.487
♪ I said. mother.
I'm afraid ♪

41
00:01:28.554 --> 00:01:30.906
♪ of the thunder
and the lightning ♪

42
00:01:30.974 --> 00:01:35.327
♪ I'll never come
through this alone ♪

43
00:01:35.394 --> 00:01:38.080
♪ she said. I'll be with you ♪

44
00:01:38.147 --> 00:01:40.666
♪ my shawl wrapped around you ♪

45
00:01:40.733 --> 00:01:45.320
♪ my hand on your head
when you go ♪

46
00:01:45.388 --> 00:01:47.422
♪ and the night came on ♪

47
00:01:47.490 --> 00:01:50.509
♪ it was very calm ♪

48
00:01:50.576 --> 00:01:52.844
♪ I wanted the night
to go on... ♪

49
00:01:52.912 --> 00:01:54.179
This is what
you're all afraid of.

50
00:01:54.246 --> 00:01:56.848
The power grid is overloaded
and gone completely down.

51
00:01:56.916 --> 00:02:00.352
plunging Los Angeles county
into near-total darkness.

52
00:02:00.419 --> 00:02:03.188
City officials
are unable or unwilling

53
00:02:03.255 --> 00:02:05.474
to speculate on when
the lights might be back on.

54
00:02:08.895 --> 00:02:11.446
Between the blackout
and the prince of darkness

55
00:02:11.531 --> 00:02:13.615
running around out there.
they advise locking doors tight

56
00:02:13.700 --> 00:02:15.984
And staying very alert.

57
00:02:16.069 --> 00:02:18.286
As one official said
off the record.

58
00:02:18.371 --> 00:02:21.506
it's going to be
a long. long night.

59
00:02:32.251 --> 00:02:34.836
Help me! Help me!

60
00:02:34.921 --> 00:02:35.837
He's coming!

61
00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:37.455
Please let me in.
Let me in.

62
00:02:37.507 --> 00:02:38.807
Let me in!
Stop!

63
00:02:38.891 --> 00:02:40.308
She's a child.
Let me in!

64
00:02:40.393 --> 00:02:42.511
Ok. I'll call--
look. I'll call the police.

65
00:02:42.595 --> 00:02:43.845
There's no time!
Do not let her in the house.

66
00:03:17.547 --> 00:03:19.848
Spicer's sister's
not in her apartment.

67
00:03:19.932 --> 00:03:21.800
The building manager
said she left hours ago.

68
00:03:21.851 --> 00:03:23.018
