tonight?

257
00:12:01.184 --> 00:12:04.052
He let you go
so that you wouldn't hurt me.

258
00:12:04.120 --> 00:12:05.804
That doesn't make you brave.

259
00:12:05.855 --> 00:12:07.990
He let me go?

260
00:12:08.074 --> 00:12:09.975
To save me.

261
00:12:12.478 --> 00:12:15.831
You're really
not like him at all.

262
00:12:20.837 --> 00:12:22.654
Get back.

263
00:12:28.094 --> 00:12:30.495
Come here.

264
00:12:30.547 --> 00:12:31.713
Come here!

265
00:12:31.798 --> 00:12:34.483
Should we kill him?

266
00:12:34.551 --> 00:12:35.684
What?

267
00:12:35.768 --> 00:12:38.136
No!

268
00:12:38.188 --> 00:12:39.271
You see. Ellie?

269
00:12:39.338 --> 00:12:40.772
We are a team.

270
00:12:40.840 --> 00:12:44.359
You just decided to
let that man live.

271
00:12:44.444 --> 00:12:49.448
Except the question
isn't why do I kill people.

272
00:12:49.515 --> 00:12:54.987
the question is
why I don't kill everybody.

273
00:12:55.038 --> 00:12:58.290
I decide who dies.

274
00:12:58.357 --> 00:13:00.542
but mostly.

275
00:13:00.627 --> 00:13:02.895
I decide who lives.

276
00:13:04.363 --> 00:13:07.382
I'm like...

277
00:13:07.467 --> 00:13:08.800
God.

278
00:13:10.303 --> 00:13:11.904
And now you are. too.

279
00:13:11.971 --> 00:13:13.722
...From L.A. police.
They're now saying

280
00:13:13.806 --> 00:13:17.559
that the prince of darkness
may be in an older white RV

281
00:13:17.644 --> 00:13:19.845
making its way around
Los Angeles tonight.

282
00:13:19.896 --> 00:13:22.731
Police are advising
that anyone seeing

283
00:13:22.815 --> 00:13:24.900
a dirty. poorly
maintained white RV

284
00:13:24.984 --> 00:13:25.934
contact them immediately.

285
00:13:26.019 --> 00:13:27.719
and do not.
under any circumstances...

286
00:13:27.770 --> 00:13:29.771
Uh-oh.
Approach it.

287
00:13:29.856 --> 00:13:31.690
What are you doing?

288
00:13:31.741 --> 00:13:35.577
Even God
finds that sometimes

289
00:13:35.662 --> 00:13:38.997
people just have
bad luck.

290
00:13:51.961 --> 00:13:54.596
Calling someone?

291
00:13:55.598 --> 00:13:57.266
Just calling triple-a.

292
00:13:57.350 --> 00:13:58.884
I got a flat.

293
00:13:58.935 --> 00:14:03.639
Just. uh.
trying to get it fixed.

294
00:14:03.723 --> 00:14:06.441
No. wait--ohh!

295
00:14:09.062 --> 00:14:11.897
Police are also saying
that the prince of darkness

296
00:14:11.948 --> 00:14:14.399
may now be traveling
with a young girl.

297
00:14:14.450 --> 00:14:17.268
an 8-year-old girl.
as a hostage.

298
00:14:17.320 --> 00:14:19.021
She's described as having
long brown hair.

299
00:14:19.088 --> 00:14:23.375
Police add that you should notify authorities
immediately if you spot her.

300
00:14:38.017 --> 00:14:39.801
All right.
what we have is an unsub

301
00:14:39.852 --> 00:14:41.302
in complete
behavioral chaos.

302
00:14:41.353 --> 00:14:42.637
Meaning?

303
00:14:42.688 --> 00:14:46.758
Serial offenders. especially long-term.
successful ones.

304
00:14:46.825 --> 00:14:49.627
don't just suddenly change what they do
or how they do it.

305
00:14:49.695 --> 00:14:51.145
Going after a high-risk target
like a police Detective

306
00:14:51.196 --> 00:14:55.033
and then all of a sudden
abducting a child is fairly unheard of.

307
00:14:55.150 --> 00:14:56.367
Fairly?
Sometimes they devolve

308
00:14:56.452 --> 00:14:57.852
as they know we're
getting closer to them

309
00:14:57.903 --> 00:14:59.037
and their time's running out.

310
00:14:59.121 --> 00:15:01.355
But this unsub doesn't
appear to be devolving.

311
00:15:01.407 --> 00:15:03.524
Devolution generally means
loss of control.

312
00:15:03.575 --> 00:15:06.411
They find it harder and harder to keep
the outside world from noticing them.

313
00:15:06.495 --> 00:15:08.496
I think he's
becoming more controlled.

314
00:15:08.547 --> 00:15:10.531
He spent a lifetime murdering
seemingly random victims.

315
00:15:10.582 --> 00:15:12.417
then out of nowhere
sought out Spicer.

316
00:15:12.501 --> 00:15:15.420
recreated his parents' murder.
lured him into a trap.

317
00:15:15.504 --> 00:15:17.088
killed him
and took his daughter.

318
00:15:17.172 --> 00:15:19.390
The behavioral spectrum
is alarmingly different.

319
00:15:23.595 --> 00:15:24.929
Yeah. Garcia.

320
00:15:25.014 --> 00:15:26.931
Hi. I want to have
better news. mon ami.

321
00:15:27.016 --> 00:15:29.100
but there are zero RVs
in the state of California

322
00:15:29.184 --> 00:15:31.602
with M-D-3 in that order
on the plate. I'm sorry.

323
00:15:31.687 --> 00:15:33.821
Sorry's not helping
anybody. I need results.

324
00:15:36.492 --> 00:15:38.893
Garcia's got nothing
on the partial plate.

325
00:15:38.944 --> 00:15:40.111
Maybe Kristin's wrong.

326
00:15:40.195 --> 00:15:41.596
It's not surprising

327
00:15:41.664 --> 00:15:43.748
considering her
situation at the time.

328
00:15:43.832 --> 00:15:45.950
So how the hell are we
supposed to find this guy?

329
00:15:46.035 --> 00:15:47.835
We can contact him.

330
00:15:57.479 --> 00:16:00.398
Leonard Cohen:
♪ dance me to your beauty ♪

331
00:16:00.466 --> 00:16:04.769
♪ with a burned violin ♪

332
00:16:04.837 --> 00:16:07.438
♪ dance me through the panic ♪

333
00:16:07.523 --> 00:16:11.592
♪ till I'm gathered safely in ♪

334
00:16:11.643 --> 00:16:15.429
♪ lift me like an olive branch ♪

335
00:16:15.481 --> 00:16:18.549
♪ be my homeward dove ♪

336
00:16:18.617 --> 00:16:20.918
♪ yeah. dance me ♪

337
00:16:20.986 --> 00:16:24.038
♪ to the end of love ♪

338
00:16:26.325 --> 00:16:27.942
♪ la la ♪

339
00:16:27.993 --> 00:16:30.778
♪ la la la la la la ♪

340
00:16:30.829 --> 00:16:32.330
...Lasers
and other technology

341
00:16:32.414 --> 00:16:34.165
so sophisticated.

342
00:16:34.249 --> 00:16:36.968
images will depict
individual telephone poles and boulders.

343
00:16:37.052 --> 00:16:40.621
Images will help determine
erosion and sea-level changes

344
00:16:40.672 --> 00:16:43.290
and also provide critical
information from flood...

345
00:16:43.342 --> 00:16:45.476
Kristin
remembered in the ambulance

346
00:16:45.561 --> 00:16:48.062
that the unsub listens
to news radio incessantly.

347
00:16:48.130 --> 00:16:50.064
He would even stop
assaulting her

348
00:16:50.132 --> 00:16:52.517
if the broadcaster said anything
about the prince of darkness.

349
00:16:52.601 --> 00:16:54.068
Makes sense
for a narcissist.

350
00:16:54.136 --> 00:16:55.069
Oh. no.

351
00:16:55.137 --> 00:16:56.070
What is it?

352
00:16:56.138 --> 00:16:57.972
The LAPD just put
all the information

353
00:16:58.023 --> 00:17:00.041
what do you mean?
They have out to the press.

354
00:17:00.109 --> 00:17:01.409
A spokesperson
at the crime scene

355
00:17:01.476 --> 00:17:02.810
was talking about the RV
and about Ellie.

356
00:17:02.878 --> 00:17:04.946
So this guy knows
exactly what we know.

357
00:17:04.997 --> 00:17:06.447
That might force him
to dump the RV.

358
00:17:06.498 --> 00:17:08.366
Or kill--

359
00:17:08.450 --> 00:17:10.701
no. I don't think so.

360
00:17:10.786 --> 00:17:11.919
Why not. Rossi?

361
00:17:11.987 --> 00:17:13.871
Well. he could have killed
you and the sister.

362
00:17:13.956 --> 00:17:16.040
He didn't.
He kept you alive.

363
00:17:16.125 --> 00:17:18.342
He can't be surprised
that we know what he's driving

364
00:17:18.427 --> 00:17:19.844
and that he has a hostage.

365
00:17:19.928 --> 00:17:22.163
But how many news radio stations
are there in Los Angeles?

366
00:17:22.214 --> 00:17:23.881
I don't know.
20 or so.

367
00:17:23.966 --> 00:17:25.633
We can't just guess
which one he listens to.

368
00:17:25.684 --> 00:17:27.185
What about
the emergency alert system?

369
00:17:27.269 --> 00:17:30.805
It would be a way to communicate over all
the stations simultaneously.

370
00:17:30.856 --> 00:17:32.039
How do we do that?

371
00:17:32.107 --> 00:17:33.858
I don't really know.
How hard could it be

372
00:17:33.942 --> 00:17:35.276
to work out?

373
00:17:43.368 --> 00:17:46.020
Is this your son's bicycle?

374
00:17:46.105 --> 00:17:48.689
What the hell...

375
00:17:48.740 --> 00:17:51.409
I--I may have
run it over.

376
00:17:51.493 --> 00:17:53.211
What'd you do.
back over it again?

377
00:17:53.295 --> 00:17:55.913
Actually. twice.

378
00:17:57.499 --> 00:17:58.883
Honey? What was that?

379
00:17:58.967 --> 00:18:00.051
Ellie.

380
00:18:01.553 --> 00:18:03.171
Paul?

381
00:18:04.807 --> 00:18:05.890
You see. Ellie?

382
00:18:05.974 --> 00:18:08.559
Bicycles mean kids.

383
00:18:08.644 --> 00:18:13.064
and kids mean parents
who are easy to control.

384
00:18:13.148 --> 00:18:15.900
So. go get the boy.

385
00:18:15.984 --> 00:18:17.768
Bring him
to the parents' room.

386
00:18:17.853 --> 00:18:19.437
Paul!
What are you gonna do?

387
00:18:19.521 --> 00:18:22.690
I have a widow to comfort.

388
00:18:22.741 --> 00:18:24.859
Go on.

389
00:18:26.778 --> 00:18:29.230
I am acutely aware that
this is an unusual request.

390
00:18:29.281 --> 00:18:31.916
It's an unusual situation.

391
00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:35.036
Then I need to speak
to your boss.

392
00:18:35.087 --> 00:18:38.422
No. I'm not calling back.
Transfer me.

393
00:18:38.507 --> 00:18:41.626
Uh. yes. who--who's this?

394
00:18:41.710 --> 00:18:44.462
Uh. and what's your title. sir?

395
00:18:44.546 --> 00:18:46.614
Ok. uh. I'm Agent
Jennifer Jareau.

396
00:18:46.682 --> 00:18:50.051
the communications liaison
for the FBI's behavioral analysis unit.

397
00:18:50.102 --> 00:18:53.221
I need access to the emergency
alert system in Los Angeles

398
00:18:53.272 --> 00:18:55.122
and I was directed
to your office.

399
00:18:55.190 --> 00:18:58.476
Yeah. the emergency
alert system.

400
00:19:00.779 --> 00:19:02.396
Get the boy in the closet.

401
00:19:02.447 --> 00:19:03.481
What?

402
00:19:03.565 --> 00:19:04.598
Do it!

403
00:19:04.650 --> 00:19:07.101
Now!

404
00:19:07.152 --> 00:19:08.769
It'll be ok. I promise.

405
00:19:08.820 --> 00:19:10.872
Don't close the door
all the way.

406
00:19:11.957 --> 00:19:14.575
What are you doing?

407
00:19:14.626 --> 00:19:16.911
I got the boy
and I got the clothes.

408
00:19:16.962 --> 00:19:18.296
So?

409
00:19:18.380 --> 00:19:19.747
So you said if I did
what you told me.

410
00:19:19.798 --> 00:19:21.382
then you'd let them live.

411
00:19:21.449 --> 00:19:24.085
Really.
Go in the bathroom

412
00:19:24.136 --> 00:19:25.386
and close the door.

413
00:19:32.761 --> 00:19:34.228
Damn it!

414
00:19:50.329 --> 00:19:53.014
He has a brother.

415
00:19:53.081 --> 00:19:55.649
I told him to tell the neighbors
to call the police

416
00:19:55.701 --> 00:19:57.084
and then tell the next house

417
00:19:57.152 --> 00:20:00.004
and the next house
and the next house.

418
00:20:00.072 --> 00:20:03.291
You know. he's probably
told the whole block by now.

419
00:20:03.342 --> 00:20:04.842
Can't kill them all. can you?

420
00:20:04.927 --> 00:20:07.111
I can try.

421
00:20:08.463 --> 00:20:10.014
Come on.

422
00:20:14.836 --> 00:20:17.171
Kristin wanted me
to tell you

423
00:20:17.222 --> 00:20:20.674
she's sorry she made you
promise her brother.

424
00:20:20.726 --> 00:20:22.693
She said it wasn't fair.

425
00:20:22.778 --> 00:20:27.148
You want to tell me what
she made you promise?

426
00:20:27.199 --> 00:20:29.734
That I wouldn't let anything
happen to Ellie.

427
00:20:31.036 --> 00:20:34.021
Well. she's right.
That's not fair.

428
00:20:34.072 --> 00:20:38.125
How is anything we handle
out here fair?

429
00:20:40.746 --> 00:20:42.546
Every time
they put me on hold.

430
00:20:42.631 --> 00:20:44.882
I get one layer higher
on homeland security.

431
00:20:44.967 --> 00:20:47.551
The E.A.S. is coordinated
by the FCC. FEMA.

432
00:20:47.636 --> 00:20:49.003
and the National
Weather Service.

433
00:20:49.054 --> 00:20:51.088
It's a bureaucratic pile
of steaming--

434
00:20:51.173 --> 00:20:53.324
yes. Yes. um. ma'am? Thank you
for holding.

435
00:20:53.392 --> 00:20:56.060
I'm with the FBI.
We're here in Los Angeles.

436
00:20:56.144 --> 00:20:57.561
A boy just woke up
his neighbors.

437
00:20:57.646 --> 00:20:59.063
Said he escaped from
the prince of darkness.

438
00:20:59.147 --> 00:21:00.848
What?

439
00:21:00.899 --> 00:21:02.433
He said they're still
in his house right now.

440
00:21:02.517 --> 00:21:04.402
There's a girl with him.
They?

441
00:21:04.486 --> 00:21:05.736
Yeah.
Let me know.

442
00:21:10.242 --> 00:21:11.242
We got you. man!

443
00:21:11.360 --> 00:21:13.077
There he is!

444
00:21:13.161 --> 00:21:14.578
That's him!

445
00:21:17.065 --> 00:21:18.699
Get in there.

446
00:21:21.370 --> 00:21:23.287
Keys.

447
00:21:23.372 --> 00:21:26.207
Always by the door.

448
00:21:26.258 --> 00:21:28.292
Come on.

449
00:21:28.377 --> 00:21:30.177
Go on.

450
00:21:31.880 --> 00:21:34.248
Go on!
Get in the car!

451
00:21:34.299 --> 00:21:36.684
Go on!

452
00:21:45.260 --> 00:21:48.029
What's the matter. scared?

453
00:21:48.096 --> 00:21:50.197
Shut up.

454
00:22:15.360 --> 00:22:17.478
The neighbors all banded together
and came after him.

455
00:22:17.529 --> 00:22:19.646
but he was already
in the car.

456
00:22:19.698 --> 00:22:21.315
Ballsy neighbors.

457
00:22:21.366 --> 00:22:23.817
California has its moments.

458
00:22:23.869 --> 00:22:26.504
The first units all got here
within 4 minutes of the call.

459
00:22:26.588 --> 00:22:29.990
Local watch commander
locked down a 5-square-mile grid

460
00:22:30.041 --> 00:22:32.009
and there's an APB
on the car.

461
00:22:32.093 --> 00:22:34.211
We believe they never
made it out of the area.

462
00:22:34.296 --> 00:22:36.847
Tell your officers not to approach him
if they spot him.

463
00:22:36.932 --> 00:22:38.449
He's getting desperate.

464
00:22:38.517 --> 00:22:41.168
Won't be easy
with a cop-killer.

465
00:22:41.219 --> 00:22:42.669
Then you'd better ask them

466
00:22:42.721 --> 00:22:45.806
how they'd feel about
getting that cop's daughter killed.

467
00:22:49.611 --> 00:22:52.062
He cut her hair.

468
00:22:53.515 --> 00:22:55.900
I swear to God. when I get my hands
on this son of a--

469
00:22:55.984 --> 00:22:57.902
that actually might be good.

470
00:22:57.986 --> 00:22:59.737
Why disguise somebody
you're gonna kill?

471
00:23:04.859 --> 00:23:07.545
Here's how he stays awake
all night.

472
00:23:09.030 --> 00:23:10.864
Look at this article
on Spicer.

473
00:23:10.916 --> 00:23:13.250
We already know he was obsessed with
all the attention Spicer was getting.

474
00:23:13.335 --> 00:23:15.202
Yeah. but look what's
underlined 3 times.

475
00:23:16.204 --> 00:23:19.039
"8-year-old Ellie.
bright. happy child."

476
00:23:20.041 --> 00:23:23.143
This one's just...

477
00:23:23.211 --> 00:23:24.445
Special.

478
00:23:26.214 --> 00:23:27.481
"I don't normally take to kids.

479
00:23:27.549 --> 00:23:29.049
but this one's just special."

480
00:23:29.100 --> 00:23:30.134
What?

481
00:23:30.202 --> 00:23:32.319
That's what he said
back at the house.

482
00:23:32.387 --> 00:23:34.772
Ellie was his target
all along. not Spicer.

483
00:23:38.726 --> 00:23:40.327
Yes. Yes. I'm still here.

484
00:23:40.395 --> 00:23:43.163
Yep. I'm always gonna be here.

485
00:23:43.231 --> 00:23:46.333
Ok. My name is Jennifer--

486
00:23:46.401 --> 00:23:47.785
no. Do you know what?

487
00:23:47.869 --> 00:23:51.622
I'm not going to explain
this entire thing again

488
00:23:51.706 --> 00:23:53.090
to another mid-level
bureaucrat

489
00:23:53.174 --> 00:23:54.575
who can't give me
a sufficient answer.

490
00:23:54.626 --> 00:23:57.545
Put someone on the damn phone
who can authorize what I need.

491
00:24:06.154 --> 00:24:07.621
He wasn't after Spicer.

492
00:24:07.689 --> 00:24:10.090
We were just coming
to the same conclusion.

493
00:24:10.158 --> 00:24:12.109
It doesn't make sense he
hasn't killed the girl

494
00:24:12.193 --> 00:24:14.111
if she wasn't
what he was after.

495
00:24:14.195 --> 00:24:15.946
He disguised her
to keep her.

496
00:24:16.031 --> 00:24:17.815
Look at this. There's
a stack of them in the RV.

497
00:24:17.899 --> 00:24:19.450
Reid's reading them all
right now.

498
00:24:19.534 --> 00:24:21.986
So. we profiled
his obsession with Spicer

499
00:24:22.070 --> 00:24:25.772
was over not getting credit
for his law enforcement career.

500
00:24:25.824 --> 00:24:29.660
But maybe it's the daughter
he's not getting credit for.

501
00:24:29.744 --> 00:24:31.962
He thinks he's
responsible for her.

502
00:24:32.047 --> 00:24:33.631
Well. she wouldn't
even be here

503
00:24:33.715 --> 00:24:36.450
if he hadn't allowed Spicer
to live 25 years ago.

504
00:24:36.501 --> 00:24:38.969
A bastardized version
of a grandparent.

505
00:24:39.054 --> 00:24:40.504
That's a pretty
twisted delusion.

506
00:24:40.589 --> 00:24:42.006
Well. it only has to
make sense to him.

507
00:24:42.090 --> 00:24:44.842
And when a delusion
like that crashes. it crashes hard.

508
00:24:44.910 --> 00:24:46.126
Hey. guys.

509
00:24:46.194 --> 00:24:48.596
The murders we found in
Orange County in 1985.

510
00:24:48.647 --> 00:24:51.015
they might not
have been his first.

511
00:24:54.302 --> 00:24:56.637
Why did you do this?
We were gonna be a--

512
00:24:56.688 --> 00:24:57.971
I told you.

513
00:24:58.023 --> 00:24:59.306
We're not a team.

514
00:24:59.357 --> 00:25:01.241
Not a team?

515
00:25:01.309 --> 00:25:02.976
We were going to--

516
00:25:08.667 --> 00:25:10.918
I was nice to you.

517
00:25:12.487 --> 00:25:14.021
The lights
are back on.

518
00:25:14.089 --> 00:25:16.657
just in time
for morning. of course.

519
00:25:16.725 --> 00:25:20.327
In other news. the noose is getting tighter
around the prince of darkness.

520
00:25:20.378 --> 00:25:23.047
The LAPD believe
they've narrowed down

521
00:25:23.131 --> 00:25:25.132
the area of the city he's in.

522
00:25:30.889 --> 00:25:32.973
Yes. I'm--

523
00:25:33.024 --> 00:25:34.308
yes. ma'am.

524
00:25:34.359 --> 00:25:36.527
Uh. yes. madame secretary.

525
00:25:36.611 --> 00:25:39.980
I'm so sorry to bother you
this early. but it's very--

526
00:25:40.031 --> 00:25:42.149
oh. you have.
Fully briefed. great.

527
00:25:42.200 --> 00:25:45.152
Um--yeah. of course.
I'm writing down the number

528
00:25:45.203 --> 00:25:46.704
right now.

529
00:25:46.788 --> 00:25:47.905
Great.

530
00:25:47.989 --> 00:25:49.907
Thank you so much.
madame secretary.

531
00:25:49.991 --> 00:25:52.910
Yeah. yeah. I will let you
know how it goes.

532
00:25:52.994 --> 00:25:54.495
Great. Thank you.

533
00:25:57.716 --> 00:25:59.083
Hotchner.

534
00:25:59.167 --> 00:26:01.385
We have access to the local
emergency alert system.

535
00:26:01.469 --> 00:26:03.870
The secretary personally
set it up herself.

536
00:26:03.922 --> 00:26:05.923
It's in the city command center.

537
00:26:06.007 --> 00:26:08.425
Good. Get an LAPD unit
to take you over there.

538
00:26:08.510 --> 00:26:09.777
get the system
up and running.

539
00:26:09.844 --> 00:26:12.179
and I need you to start
talking to him immediately.

540
00:26:12.230 --> 00:26:13.430
Excuse me?

541
00:26:13.515 --> 00:26:15.599
It's gonna take me too long
to get there from here.

542
00:26:15.684 --> 00:26:17.101
I need you to talk to him. JJ.

543
00:26:17.185 --> 00:26:19.186
I'll give you
some strategies.
Me?

544
00:26:19.237 --> 00:26:20.437
The unsub may still be
in this area.

545
00:26:20.522 --> 00:26:22.106
and if he surfaces.
we need to be close.

546
00:26:22.190 --> 00:26:24.558
I'm not a hostage negotiator.

547
00:26:24.609 --> 00:26:27.027
I'm sorry. You are today.

548
00:26:31.548 --> 00:26:33.132
Dr. Reid.
you're on your own cellular.

549
00:26:33.217 --> 00:26:34.717
Yeah. The power came
back here a few minutes ago.

550
00:26:35.739 --> 00:26:37.139
How's my main man doing?

551
00:26:37.207 --> 00:26:38.507
On the completely
safe assumption

552
00:26:38.575 --> 00:26:39.792
that you're not
talking about me.

553
00:26:39.877 --> 00:26:41.794
let's just say I wouldn't want
to be this unsub

554
00:26:41.879 --> 00:26:43.245
when Morgan finally
gets his hands on him.

555
00:26:43.297 --> 00:26:44.580
That bad. huh?

556
00:26:44.631 --> 00:26:46.081
Has he ever yelled
at you before?

557
00:26:46.133 --> 00:26:47.884
Touche.

558
00:26:47.951 --> 00:26:49.251
How can I be of service?

559
00:26:49.303 --> 00:26:52.088
How far back can you go
with your records. Garcia?

560
00:26:52.155 --> 00:26:53.823
How far back you talkin'?

561
00:26:53.891 --> 00:26:56.859
Uh. a murder investigation
from 1968.

562
00:27:00.898 --> 00:27:02.565
This is the room.

563
00:27:05.268 --> 00:27:06.435
So what do I do?

564
00:27:06.486 --> 00:27:08.287
Flip that switch
when you're ready.

565
00:27:08.372 --> 00:27:09.789
and you'll cut into
every signal

566
00:27:09.873 --> 00:27:11.941
on the radio bands.
am and fm.

567
00:27:11.992 --> 00:27:13.108
That's it?

568
00:27:13.160 --> 00:27:14.944
It's made to be easy.

569
00:27:14.995 --> 00:27:17.163
Ok. Thank you.

570
00:27:27.307 --> 00:27:28.474
JJ.

571
00:27:28.558 --> 00:27:29.625
I'm here.

572
00:27:29.676 --> 00:27:31.126
We're gathering some
background information

573
00:27:31.178 --> 00:27:32.612
on Flynn that could be
very helpful.

574
00:27:32.679 --> 00:27:34.630
Ok.
Just sit tight for a minute.

575
00:27:34.681 --> 00:27:35.848
You ok?

576
00:27:35.933 --> 00:27:37.967
Hotch...

577
00:27:38.018 --> 00:27:39.685
What if I mess up?

578
00:27:39.770 --> 00:27:42.137
Don't worry. You won't.

579
00:27:42.189 --> 00:27:43.990
I'll call you right back.

580
00:27:48.528 --> 00:27:51.747
♪ Oh. the sisters of mercy ♪

581
00:27:51.815 --> 00:27:56.419
♪ they are not departed
or gone ♪

582
00:27:59.706 --> 00:28:02.425
♪ they were waiting for me ♪

583
00:28:02.492 --> 00:28:06.662
♪ when I thought
that I just can't go on ♪

584
00:28:10.333 --> 00:28:13.269
♪ and they brought me
their comfort ♪

585
00:28:13.336 --> 00:28:18.941
♪ and later they
brought me this song ♪

586
00:28:27.200 --> 00:28:28.617
Now...

587
00:28:28.685 --> 00:28:30.653
Get inside.

588
00:28:35.909 --> 00:28:39.795
Get inside and don't come
out until I call for you!

589
00:28:48.138 --> 00:28:49.055
Already?

590
00:28:49.139 --> 00:28:50.222
Do you doubt it?

591
00:28:50.307 --> 00:28:52.207
Yeah. I'll put you
on speaker.

592
00:28:52.259 --> 00:28:54.209
Ok. Let me preface this
by saying

593
00:28:54.261 --> 00:28:56.712
that a 40-year-old murder
in a suburb of Los Angeles

594
00:28:56.763 --> 00:28:58.514
is an absurdly
impossible request.

595
00:28:58.565 --> 00:29:01.717
Having said that. yours truly happens to know
that the Pollack Library at Cal State--

596
00:29:01.768 --> 00:29:02.718
Garcia.

597
00:29:02.769 --> 00:29:03.736
Yes. sir. sorry. uh...

598
00:29:03.820 --> 00:29:06.221
Anyway. this murder
was quite the scandal.

599
00:29:06.273 --> 00:29:08.908
For Southern California in the sixties.
that's saying something.

600
00:29:08.992 --> 00:29:11.410
Ok. I don't know
who was talking right then.

601
00:29:11.495 --> 00:29:13.079
but...Word.

602
00:29:13.163 --> 00:29:16.949
So. Nora Flynn was a prostitute
and a drug addict

603
00:29:17.034 --> 00:29:20.402
living in a desert community
just outside of Los Angeles.

604
00:29:20.454 --> 00:29:23.873
It appears bikers were her stock in trade.
rough bikers.

605
00:29:23.924 --> 00:29:26.258
and one fateful day.
she and her client

606
00:29:26.343 --> 00:29:27.927
were murdered by
her 13-year-old son Billy.

607
00:29:28.011 --> 00:29:29.211
Shot to death.

608
00:29:29.262 --> 00:29:30.596
The customer.
ironically named John.

609
00:29:30.680 --> 00:29:32.431
was able to tell the police
before he died

610
00:29:32.516 --> 00:29:34.767
that Billy made him beg for his life
and then shot him anyway.

611
00:29:34.851 --> 00:29:36.418
That's him.

612
00:29:36.470 --> 00:29:37.720
And he was
convicted. but...

613
00:29:37.771 --> 00:29:38.938
Right.
He's a juvenile.

614
00:29:39.005 --> 00:29:41.423
So at 18.
he was released in 1973.

615
00:29:41.475 --> 00:29:42.608
never heard from again.

616
00:29:42.692 --> 00:29:43.943
Oh. he was heard from.

617
00:29:44.027 --> 00:29:45.361
And he never released
a statement

618
00:29:45.428 --> 00:29:46.562
as to why
he killed them.

619
00:29:46.613 --> 00:29:49.098
although it does appear
his childhood was horrific.

620
00:29:49.149 --> 00:29:52.101
I'm sending you a picture of him on the day
he was released to your PDAS.

621
00:29:52.152 --> 00:29:54.453
Make sure you send
the files to JJ.

622
00:29:54.538 --> 00:29:55.454
Of course. my liege.

623
00:29:55.539 --> 00:29:56.622
Garcia bids you ad--

624
00:29:56.706 --> 00:29:58.791
Garcia. wait a minute.

625
00:30:02.712 --> 00:30:04.113
Hey.

626
00:30:04.164 --> 00:30:05.297
Hey back.

627
00:30:05.382 --> 00:30:07.133
Baby girl. I'm sorry
for taking your head off.

628
00:30:07.200 --> 00:30:08.784
Oh. darling.
our love is a rock.

629
00:30:08.835 --> 00:30:10.503
No bad day can come
between us.

630
00:30:10.587 --> 00:30:11.504
Word.

631
00:30:12.722 --> 00:30:13.973
Come home safe.

632
00:30:14.057 --> 00:30:15.391
I'll leave a light on.

633
00:30:19.346 --> 00:30:20.312
Hotch.

634
00:30:20.397 --> 00:30:21.981
JJ. listen.

635
00:30:22.065 --> 00:30:24.817
The most important thing
is that you build rapport with him.

636
00:30:24.901 --> 00:30:26.485
Uh. rapport. Ok.

637
00:30:26.570 --> 00:30:28.320
I'm asking you to do
one of the hardest things

638
00:30:28.405 --> 00:30:30.489
that anybody in our position
ever has to do.

639
00:30:30.574 --> 00:30:33.292
I need you to empathize
with him. Sympathize.

640
00:30:33.360 --> 00:30:35.311
Don't judge
the things he's done.

641
00:30:35.378 --> 00:30:37.329
Garcia's sending you a file
on him and his childhood.

642
00:30:37.414 --> 00:30:38.864
Look it over. It'll help.

643
00:30:38.949 --> 00:30:40.332
If he hears
that you care about him.

644
00:30:40.417 --> 00:30:42.802
that's how you're gonna
get him to care about Ellie.

645
00:30:42.869 --> 00:30:45.955
He has to understand that he's putting her
through the same pain

646
00:30:46.006 --> 00:30:47.406
he went through as a child.

647
00:30:48.675 --> 00:30:50.292
Uh. ok.

648
00:30:50.343 --> 00:30:51.977
But it has to be
his decision

649
00:30:52.045 --> 00:30:53.829
because power
is all-important to him.

650
00:30:53.880 --> 00:30:55.514
Power? Ok.

651
00:30:55.599 --> 00:30:56.999
You're gonna be fine.

652
00:30:57.067 --> 00:30:58.317
Just talk to him.

653
00:30:58.385 --> 00:30:59.502
All right.

654
00:30:59.569 --> 00:31:01.470
Go over the file
and start when you're ready.

655
00:31:01.521 --> 00:31:03.956
Oh. wait. You're gonna
be on the line. right?

656
00:31:04.024 --> 00:31:05.858
I'll be listening.

657
00:31:12.699 --> 00:31:15.401
And the heat wave continues to be
the top story in the Southland.

658
00:31:15.485 --> 00:31:18.370
with temperatures expected
to top 105 degrees.

659
00:31:18.455 --> 00:31:20.306
and excessive heat...

660
00:31:22.209 --> 00:31:25.911
Come on. Billy.
I bought you from your mama.

661
00:31:25.996 --> 00:31:28.080
This man paid
good money.

662
00:31:28.165 --> 00:31:29.632
Mom! No!

663
00:31:29.699 --> 00:31:31.283
Do as you're told!

664
00:31:32.419 --> 00:31:33.869
Mom! Make him stop!

665
00:31:35.222 --> 00:31:37.239
I'll be gentle. Billy.
Don't worry.

666
00:31:37.307 --> 00:31:39.475
No!

667
00:31:41.344 --> 00:31:43.062
Billy?

668
00:31:43.146 --> 00:31:45.264
Billy Flynn?

669
00:31:45.348 --> 00:31:46.265
Did you--

670
00:31:46.349 --> 00:31:47.883
who's Billy Flynn?

671
00:31:47.934 --> 00:31:50.385
Mr. Flynn. I--
I don't know for sure

672
00:31:50.437 --> 00:31:51.687
that you can hear me. but--

673
00:31:51.738 --> 00:31:53.422
my name is Jennifer Jareau.

674
00:31:53.490 --> 00:31:56.692
I--I work for the FBI
as a communications liaison

675
00:31:56.743 --> 00:32:01.113
for the--the behavioral. uh...

676
00:32:01.198 --> 00:32:03.115
Ok. Mr. Flynn. I--

677
00:32:03.200 --> 00:32:07.786
I--I want to talk to you
about letting Ellie Spicer go.

678
00:32:07.871 --> 00:32:10.873
I mean. I want to ask you to.

679
00:32:10.924 --> 00:32:15.294
Uh. see. I'm not
a hostage negotiator. uh.

680
00:32:15.378 --> 00:32:18.797
I've never done anything
like this at all ever.

681
00:32:18.882 --> 00:32:23.352
but. um. sometimes
circumstances. it's...

682
00:32:25.388 --> 00:32:27.756
Look...

683
00:32:27.807 --> 00:32:32.895
You can tell I'm not
a hostage negotiator.

684
00:32:32.946 --> 00:32:36.365
But I am a mother.

685
00:32:36.432 --> 00:32:38.951
And I...

686
00:32:39.035 --> 00:32:42.821
I know what your mother
did to you when you were little.

687
00:32:42.906 --> 00:32:45.274
What she was.

688
00:32:45.342 --> 00:32:49.461
what she made you watch.
what she let men do to you.

689
00:32:49.546 --> 00:32:52.614
and it makes me so...

690
00:32:52.666 --> 00:32:57.253
It's just not fair.

691
00:32:57.304 --> 00:32:59.454
And no one--
no one can make that better.

692
00:32:59.506 --> 00:33:01.507
I wish I could. I do. But...

693
00:33:01.591 --> 00:33:03.625
If I--if I could somehow
go back there

694
00:33:03.677 --> 00:33:07.963
and. you know. make what was
happening to you stop.

695
00:33:08.014 --> 00:33:09.464
if I could just...

696
00:33:09.516 --> 00:33:13.468
You know. pick you up
and just tell you

697
00:33:13.520 --> 00:33:15.321
that it'll all be ok.

698
00:33:15.405 --> 00:33:19.308
That's what moms
are supposed to do.

699
00:33:19.359 --> 00:33:21.810
They're not supposed to be
the cause of your pain.

700
00:33:21.861 --> 00:33:24.646
they're supposed to
make it go away.

701
00:33:24.698 --> 00:33:26.481
They're supposed to hold you

702
00:33:26.533 --> 00:33:30.485
and tell you everything
is gonna be all right.

703
00:33:30.537 --> 00:33:35.157
They're supposed to tell you
that thunder is Angels bowling

704
00:33:35.208 --> 00:33:37.209
and that it's ok
to be afraid of the dark

705
00:33:37.294 --> 00:33:40.462
and that it's not silly
to think there might be

706
00:33:40.513 --> 00:33:42.331
monsters in your closet
and that it's ok

707
00:33:42.382 --> 00:33:44.850
that if you want to climb in bed with them
just this once.

708
00:33:44.934 --> 00:33:50.522
'cause it's scary
in the room all alone.

709
00:33:50.607 --> 00:33:53.275
They're supposed to say
it's ok to be afraid.

710
00:33:53.343 --> 00:33:55.644
and not be the thing
you're afraid of.

711
00:33:55.695 --> 00:33:58.113
But most importantly.

712
00:33:58.181 --> 00:34:02.067
they're supposed to love you
no matter what.

713
00:34:02.152 --> 00:34:05.037
What happened to you
isn't fair. it's not right.

714
00:34:05.121 --> 00:34:08.040
but. um...

715
00:34:08.124 --> 00:34:12.461
I'm supposed to empathize
with you.

716
00:34:12.528 --> 00:34:16.965
Sympathize. Understand.

717
00:34:17.033 --> 00:34:18.367
But I can't.

718
00:34:18.418 --> 00:34:20.035
That--that would be a lie.

719
00:34:20.086 --> 00:34:23.305
The truth is. I don't
understand what you've done.

720
00:34:23.373 --> 00:34:27.393
I don't sympathize with you killing people
all these years.

721
00:34:27.477 --> 00:34:30.512
And I especially don't
understand you taking Ellie.

722
00:34:30.563 --> 00:34:34.149
What I can do is tell you
what a mother should tell you.

723
00:34:34.217 --> 00:34:36.485
that you can't
take away your pain

724
00:34:36.552 --> 00:34:37.770
by hurting someone else.

725
00:34:37.854 --> 00:34:39.554
That it doesn't make
all the nights

726
00:34:39.606 --> 00:34:41.357
you went to bed
scared and alone

727
00:34:41.408 --> 00:34:43.058
any better if you
scare someone else

728
00:34:43.109 --> 00:34:44.910
the way you're scaring Ellie.

729
00:34:44.994 --> 00:34:47.079
What happened to you.
it isn't fair.

730
00:34:47.163 --> 00:34:49.281
But what you're doing
to her isn't fair either.

731
00:34:49.366 --> 00:34:52.067
and if anyone should
understand what that feels like.

732
00:34:52.118 --> 00:34:54.920
it's you.

733
00:34:55.004 --> 00:34:57.122
You have the power.

734
00:34:57.207 --> 00:35:01.760
You can do
what you want to do.

735
00:35:01.845 --> 00:35:03.762
But for once.

736
00:35:03.847 --> 00:35:07.299
you can choose
to use that power

737
00:35:07.384 --> 00:35:10.436
to do for Ellie what should have
been done for you.

738
00:35:10.520 --> 00:35:14.640
You can choose
letting her go.

739
00:35:14.724 --> 00:35:16.275
You can choose teaching her

740
00:35:16.359 --> 00:35:18.977
that. yes.
there are monsters.

741
00:35:19.062 --> 00:35:22.114
and it's ok
to be afraid of them.

742
00:35:22.198 --> 00:35:25.984
But it's not ok
to let them win.

743
00:35:26.069 --> 00:35:28.721
And it's not ok to be one.

744
00:35:42.051 --> 00:35:43.952
Agent Prentiss.

745
00:35:44.003 --> 00:35:45.804
Yes. Hello. doctor.

746
00:35:48.224 --> 00:35:49.791
Yes. sir.

747
00:35:49.843 --> 00:35:51.960
Thank you.

748
00:35:52.011 --> 00:35:55.013
Both of Kristin's lungs
collapsed.

749
00:35:55.098 --> 00:35:56.231
She died a few minutes ago.

750
00:35:57.317 --> 00:35:58.317
Ellie's got no one now.

751
00:35:58.401 --> 00:35:59.651
Kurzbard.

752
00:35:59.736 --> 00:36:01.270
He let her go.

753
00:36:01.321 --> 00:36:03.188
Where?

754
00:36:03.273 --> 00:36:06.475
He got out of the car
and he just let her go.

755
00:36:06.526 --> 00:36:08.494
She's in a house about
6 blocks from here.

756
00:36:08.578 --> 00:36:09.611
Where is he now?

757
00:36:09.662 --> 00:36:12.448
He's in another house.
up the street.

758
00:36:15.602 --> 00:36:17.719
JJ. I don't know if you know.
You did it.

759
00:36:30.283 --> 00:36:31.817
We have SWAT
on the way. Kurz.

760
00:36:31.901 --> 00:36:33.152
And an HPT team.

761
00:36:33.236 --> 00:36:34.936
Yeah. but they'll
be a while.

762
00:36:34.988 --> 00:36:36.789
We had a phone sent in
with a direct line to this one.

763
00:36:36.873 --> 00:36:38.457
But so far--

764
00:36:39.492 --> 00:36:42.110
He's watching us.

765
00:36:42.162 --> 00:36:44.997
This is Detective Kurzbard.
LAPD.

766
00:36:48.134 --> 00:36:50.169
He wants to talk to you.

767
00:36:53.223 --> 00:36:54.556
What?

768
00:37:00.063 --> 00:37:01.980
He wants me to come in.

769
00:37:02.065 --> 00:37:03.098
Morgan.

770
00:37:05.101 --> 00:37:06.568
I know this guy. Hotch.

771
00:37:06.636 --> 00:37:08.821
He didn't kill me before.
he's not gonna kill me this time.

772
00:37:08.905 --> 00:37:09.988
No.

773
00:37:10.073 --> 00:37:11.940
I believe in
my original profile.

774
00:37:11.991 --> 00:37:14.276
He will not hurt me
unless I show him fear.

775
00:37:14.327 --> 00:37:15.360
Listen--

776
00:37:15.445 --> 00:37:16.829
when you needed us.
we were there for you.

777
00:37:16.913 --> 00:37:18.780
This one is mine.

778
00:37:18.832 --> 00:37:20.916
You sure?

779
00:37:20.983 --> 00:37:22.484
As I've ever been.

780
00:37:48.194 --> 00:37:51.113
In here. Agent.

781
00:38:26.399 --> 00:38:28.250
It's over. Flynn.

782
00:38:28.318 --> 00:38:30.018
5 years ago.

783
00:38:30.069 --> 00:38:32.821
I would have just killed you

784
00:38:32.888 --> 00:38:35.540
right there
in that bedroom.

785
00:38:35.608 --> 00:38:37.892
You couldn't.

786
00:38:37.944 --> 00:38:39.077
Couldn't?

787
00:38:43.333 --> 00:38:45.017
I'm not afraid of you.

788
00:38:48.237 --> 00:38:50.973
You really think that matters
that much to me?

789
00:38:51.040 --> 00:38:52.240
Then shoot me.

790
00:38:52.308 --> 00:38:56.094
Go ahead. Shoot me.

791
00:38:59.766 --> 00:39:02.017
You can't do it.

792
00:39:02.085 --> 00:39:03.785
I study guys like you
for a living.

793
00:39:03.853 --> 00:39:06.355
I know more about you
than you know about yourself.

794
00:39:08.942 --> 00:39:12.644
Well. you may not be afraid.
but they are.

795
00:39:12.729 --> 00:39:15.697
You point that gun at them
and I will kill you.

796
00:39:15.765 --> 00:39:17.482
and that is another promise.

797
00:39:17.550 --> 00:39:22.037
My mother
used to dance with me.

798
00:39:22.104 --> 00:39:25.324
You know who
Cyd Charisse was?

799
00:39:26.943 --> 00:39:29.277
She kind of
looked like her.

800
00:39:29.329 --> 00:39:32.030
Put the gun down
and get up.

801
00:39:32.098 --> 00:39:34.883
When I shot her...

802
00:39:37.286 --> 00:39:40.722
She looked at me
with such...

803
00:39:43.459 --> 00:39:47.012
She was...

804
00:39:47.096 --> 00:39:50.965
I think relieved.

805
00:39:51.017 --> 00:39:53.885
I think I helped her escape.

806
00:39:56.305 --> 00:40:00.308
Was that really true.
or did I just imagine it.

807
00:40:00.360 --> 00:40:04.379
to make killing her
easier to live with?

808
00:40:05.848 --> 00:40:09.167
Did I help her escape?

809
00:40:09.252 --> 00:40:11.870
Did I...

810
00:40:11.954 --> 00:40:16.041
Set her free?

811
00:40:16.125 --> 00:40:18.660
Is that what you think you've
been doing all these years.

812
00:40:18.711 --> 00:40:20.379
helping people?

813
00:40:24.717 --> 00:40:27.686
Well. no. I suppose not.

814
00:40:27.770 --> 00:40:31.005
Do you believe in heaven?

815
00:40:32.675 --> 00:40:35.077
This is your last chance.

816
00:40:38.815 --> 00:40:43.518
You think I might
see her there?

817
00:40:43.569 --> 00:40:46.855
Maybe get
a second chance?

818
00:40:57.333 --> 00:40:59.051
I'd really like that.

819
